title: MUNNAGAI WOGGABALIRI
description: Munnagai Woggabaliri, in the Aboriginal language of the Ngunawal people, means come play.

title: YERRADHANG NGURU
description: Yerradhang Nguru, in the Aboriginal language of the Ngunawal people, means Gumtree Camp.

title: BUNBURUNG THINA
description: Bunburung Thina is the central green parklands that meander through the heart of Googong.

title: ALWAYS WAS ALWAYS WILL BE
description: The area now known as Googong has a rich cultural history for the traditional custodians.

title: HIA AWARD WINS
description: Vogue Constructions took out Display Home of the Year (under $500,000) and People's Choice awards at the prestigious HIA ACT Awards.

title: GOOGONG DISPLAY VILLAGE OPENS
description: The biggest display village in the region will open in Googong on Saturday 31 October, giving potential home buyers more choice than ever when it comes to planning for their future home. The 19 display homes have been built by 15 different builders.

title: RECYCLED WATER AT GOOGONG
description: QPRC have completed extensive testing and commissioning of Googong's Integrated Water Cycle (IWC) system, and will host a community education program with residents over the coming weeks before reticulation of recycled water commences on Tuesday 1 December 2020.

title: GOOGONG WINS PROPERTY COUNCIL AWARD
description: The developers of Googong township are thrilled to announce that Googong has taken home the ACT’s top property award.

title: CENTRAL RIDGE RELEASE
description: Our new land release, Googong Central, offers you the simplicity and convenience of living within 200 metres of Googong's future town centre.

title: PARKSIDE RELEASE
description: Our Parkside land release is enviably located on the edge of Googong Common, and Googong's future sports precinct.

title: GOOGONIAN GAZETTE OUT NOW
description: Our August issue is out now!

title: HOMESTEAD HILL RELEASE
description: Homestead Hill enjoys stunning views to the Molonglo Ranges, and includes a mix of large and elevated lots.

title: LOTS TO LOVE
description: Two uniquely spacious suburban lots overlooking a pristine nature reserve.

title: GOOGONG GIGS WITH LUCY SUGERMAN
description: This month's Googong Gig's features the enormously talented singer-songwriter, Lucy Sugerman.

title: EVENTS IN 2020
description: After careful consideration we have made the decision to cancel most of our community and public events for the remainder of 2020 due to concerns and uncertainties surrounding COVID-19.

title: FHB STAMP DUTY SLASHED
description: NSW Government announced a big boost for first home buyers.

title: ELLERTON DRIVE EXTENSION OPENED
description: The ribbon has been cut and the finishing touches applied and now the new Ellerton Drive extension is open to traffic.

title: ARCHAEOLOGICAL SITE VISIT OF GOOGONG'S FIRST SCHOOL
description: The public are invited to attend an archaeological dig site of Googong's first school (c.1880's). Places are strictly limited and bookings and conditions apply.
